  "observation": "Brainstorm triggered by plateau. 4 proposals generated.",
  "suggestion": "The plateau likely reflects that organisms have found locally-optimal form within a static 1D or 2D beauty landscape. They've maxed out morphological variation without new selection pressures. The system needs DIMENSIONALITY EXPANSION — add temporal dynamics (motion, growth, lineage), collective behaviors (colonies, symbiosis), and real resource constraints (energy, light, predation). Each adds a new axis of competition. Evolution restarts its search in higher-dimensional space.; [medium] Introduce multi-scale temporal beauty metric: beauty computed not just on instantaneous form, but on motion patterns, group synchronization, and multi-generational aesthetic lineage. Add cell type that records organism history (ancestor chain). Beauty now rewards both individual form AND how gracefully organisms move AND how their offspring refine their parent's design. — Current beauty metric is likely static/snapshot-based. Organisms have saturated single-frame aesthetics. Temporal beauty adds infinite dimensionality — a trajectory through beauty-space rather than a point. Breaks plateau by opening new selection pressure on dynamics and inheritance.; [hard] Add symbiosis mechanic: new cell type (signaling cell) that allows organisms to form temporary multi-organism colonies. Colonies compete as units. Beauty/fitness now scores not just individual organisms but emergent group patterns. Organisms can evolve complementary roles (some cells specialize in beautifying outer shell, others in reproduction, others in nutrition). — Current evolution is single-organism focused. Plateau may reflect that individual morphology space is exhausted. Multi-organism colonies and role specialization open vastly larger solution space. Fitness reward for coordination encourages new morphologies (e.g., long chains, wheel formations, fractal nesting).; [hard] Overhaul world energy model: replace static energy distribution with active photosynthetic cell type that converts world light → organism energy in real-time. Make light anisotropic (sun moves, seasons exist). Organisms must now evolve not just for beauty but to *harvest* energy efficiently while remaining beautiful. Create actual predator-prey trophic cascade. — Current fitness may be too 'free' — organisms aren't competing for scarce resources, just optimizing abstract metrics. Adding real energy scarcity + dynamic light creates new selective pressure: how do you stay alive AND beautiful? Organisms currently may be over-investing in beauty at survival cost, or vice versa. Real tradeoffs break plateaus.",
